I'm headed to North Korea.

00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:31.190
That's my next film.

00:23:31.190 --> 00:23:33.340
Seriously if I could
do that, yeah.

00:23:33.340 --> 00:23:36.850
I did the second most isolated
country, and I think that

00:23:36.850 --> 00:23:40.260
there's a need to have some
sort of perspective on the

00:23:40.260 --> 00:23:42.420
situation in North Korea.

00:23:42.420 --> 00:23:44.380
It's gotten a little hysterical,
as you're probably

00:23:44.380 --> 00:23:47.040
aware, and so I feel like,
oh, that would be a

00:23:47.040 --> 00:23:48.790
neat place to go.

00:23:48.790 --> 00:23:52.490
There are real environmental
problems that exist in Burma.

00:23:52.490 --> 00:23:55.340
First of all, the timber
is being cut.

00:23:55.340 --> 00:23:58.240
These are the last of the
great teak forests, and

00:23:58.240 --> 00:24:02.130
they're being cut down, and it's
not sustainable, and the

00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:05.980
logging is illegal.

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:09.980
Inle Lake, you'll see this
beautiful lake in the movie,

00:24:09.980 --> 00:24:11.440
and they grow tomatoes on it.

00:24:11.440 --> 00:24:14.460
They have floating vegetable
gardens.

00:24:14.460 --> 00:24:17.140
Essentially, the detritus
washes down from the

00:24:17.140 --> 00:24:21.180
mountains, and it floats, and
they have tomato plants, and

00:24:21.180 --> 00:24:23.920
you get to them with a boat,
and you can work on them.

00:24:23.920 --> 00:24:26.480
The trouble, it's all beautiful,
but they're using

00:24:26.480 --> 00:24:32.440
pesticides, and the lake is
seriously polluted, so that's

00:24:32.440 --> 00:24:34.150
one environmental concern.

00:24:34.150 --> 00:24:36.920
There's a big project
in the works.

00:24:36.920 --> 00:24:42.560
There is a Thai-Italian company
that is prepared to

00:24:42.560 --> 00:24:45.490
develop Dawei.

00:24:45.490 --> 00:24:48.320
It is going to be a development
which is four

00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:50.710
times the size of Manhattan.

00:24:50.710 --> 00:24:52.530
It's petrochemical.

00:24:52.530 --> 00:24:58.030
There are going to be roads
linking Dawei with Thailand.

00:24:58.030 --> 00:25:01.790
The Chinese are building a
railroad, which will go from

00:25:01.790 --> 00:25:05.000
Dawei up into Yenon.

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:08.410
Dawei is situated in such a
place where boats coming can

00:25:08.410 --> 00:25:10.080
avoid the Straits of Malacca.

00:25:10.080 --> 00:25:15.730
It's a fast run to China, and
so why are they doing this.

00:25:15.730 --> 00:25:18.020
Why are the Thais involved
building Dawei?

00:25:18.020 --> 00:25:21.770
Well, because of pollution
controls in Thailand.

00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:24.180
They can get away with much
more than they could in

00:25:24.180 --> 00:25:26.790
Thailand, and if you've been
in Thailand, then you

00:25:26.790 --> 00:25:27.350
understand.

00:25:27.350 --> 00:25:30.790
Been in Bangkok and know what
the pollution is like there,

00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:35.590
you can see that this is just
a disaster in the making.

00:25:35.590 --> 00:25:37.950
The Chinese are building
dams on--

00:25:37.950 --> 00:25:41.360
there was a big project, the
Myitsone dam, which was going

00:25:41.360 --> 00:25:46.070
to be built by the Chinese, and
it has been put on hold.

00:25:46.070 --> 00:25:48.050
Or I don't know if it's been
canceled or not, but there are

00:25:48.050 --> 00:25:49.590
other dams going in.

00:25:49.590 --> 00:25:53.290
There's been really popular
uprising against these dams.

00:25:56.005 --> 00:25:57.500
What's the future
of the country?

00:25:57.500 --> 00:26:02.240
Well, the country really needs
experts, and not just Western

00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:06.070
experts, but it needs Burmese
who know what's going on, and

00:26:06.070 --> 00:26:07.760
can speak the language.

00:26:07.760 --> 00:26:11.230
And there are huge Burmese
communities here

00:26:11.230 --> 00:26:12.170
in the United States.

00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:15.150
The people there are educated.

00:26:15.150 --> 00:26:21.900
They know banking, they know
medicine, but the question is,

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:23.830
will they come back?

00:26:23.830 --> 00:26:29.570
The military has a get out of
jail for free card, but the

00:26:29.570 --> 00:26:31.170
dissidents don't.

