Well, I'm probably not the guy
to answer it, but I mean,

00:35:56.996 --> 00:35:59.020
there were the original
indigenous

00:35:59.020 --> 00:36:01.210
populations that were--

00:36:01.210 --> 00:36:02.130
whoops, the map is gone.

00:36:02.130 --> 00:36:05.980
Anyhow, there was also,
essentially, from Tibet

00:36:05.980 --> 00:36:07.070
populations came down.

00:36:07.070 --> 00:36:08.400
There was all this mixing.

00:36:08.400 --> 00:36:09.920
I don't really know.

00:36:09.920 --> 00:36:11.500
I'm not a linguist.

00:36:11.500 --> 00:36:17.000
Yeah, anyhow, I'm afraid to
answer that question.

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:18.550
I'm always amazed that
people speak

00:36:18.550 --> 00:36:20.900
different languages, right.

00:36:20.900 --> 00:36:24.610
And children growing up invent
their own words, right,

00:36:24.610 --> 00:36:27.200
because we're hardwired
for language somehow.

